"2066","Mari Casas."
"2067","Section 17. Questions of Interpretation. Any question of"
"2068","interpretation of any term or provision of this Agreement having a"
"2069","counterpart in or otherwise derived from a term or provision of the 1940"
"2070","Act shall be resolved by reference to such terms or provision of the 1940"
"2071","Act and to interpretations thereof, if any, by the United States Courts or in"
"2072","the absence of any controlling decision of any such court, by rules,"
"2073","regulations or orders of the Commission, or interpretations of the"
"2074","Commission or its staff, or Commission staff no-action letters, issued"
"2075","pursuant to the 1940 Act. In addition, where the effect of a requirement of"
"2076","the 1940 Act or the Advisers Act reflected in any provision of this"
"2077","Agreement is revised by rule, regulation or order of the Commission, such"
"2078","provision shall be deemed to incorporate the effect of such rule, regulation"
"2079","or order. The duties and obligations of the parties under this Agreement"
"2080","shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the"
"2081","State of Delaware."
"2082","Section 18. Amendment. This Agreement supersedes the subadvisory"
"2083","agreement among Wells Fargo Funds Trust, Wells Fargo Bank,"
"2084","N.A. and Wells Fargo Capital Management Incorporated dated November"
"2085","8, 1999, as approved by the Board of Trustees on March 26, 1999 as"
"2086","amended October 28, 1999, May 9, 2000 and July 25, 2000. No provision"
"2087","of this Agreement may be changed, waived, discharged or terminated"
"2088","orally, but only by an instrument in writing signed by the party against"
"2089","which enforcement of the change, waiver, discharge or termination is"
"2090","sought. If shareholder approval of an amendment is required under the"
"2091","1940 Act, no such amendment shall become effective until approved by a"
"2092","vote of the majority of the outstanding shares of the affected Funds."
"2093","Otherwise, a written amendment of this Agreement is effective upon the"
"2094","approval of the Board of Trustees, the Adviser and the Sub-Adviser."
"2095","Section 19. Wells Fargo Name. The Sub-Adviser and the Trust"
"2096","each agree that the name Wells Fargo, which comprises a component of"
"2097","the Trust's name, is a property right of the parent of the Adviser. The"
"2098","Trust agrees and consents that: (i) it will use the words Wells Fargo as a"
"2099","component of its corporate name, the name of any series or class, or all of"
"2100","the above, and for no other purpose; (ii) it will not grant to any third party"
"2101","the right to use the name Wells Fargo for any purpose; (iii) the Adviser"
"2102","or any corporate affiliate of the Adviser may use or grant to others the"
"2103","right to use the words Wells Fargo, or any combination or abbreviation"
"2104","thereof, as all or a portion of a corporate or business name or for any"
"2105","commercial purpose, other than a grant of such right to another registered"
"2106","investment company not advised by the Adviser or one of its affiliates;"
"2107","and (iv) in the event that the Adviser or an affiliate thereof is no longer"
"2108","acting as investment adviser to any Fund or class of a Fund, the Trust"
"2109","shall, upon request by the Adviser, promptly take such action as may be"
"2110","necessary to change its corporate name to one not containing the words"
"2111","Wells Fargo and following such change, shall not use the words Wells
Fargo, or any combination thereof, as a part of its corporate name or for"
"2112","any other commercial purpose, and shall use its best efforts to cause its"
"2113","trustees, officers and shareholders to take any and all actions that the"
"2114","Adviser may request to effect the foregoing and to reconvey to the Adviser"
"2115","any and all rights to such words."
